         MACRO
         ADCB  ,
ADCB     DSECT ,
*
ADCBDATA DS    0CL256  DESCRIPTION OF ENTIRE ADCB
ADCBID   DC    C'ADCB' ADCB IDENTIFICATION
*
*      THE ADCB (ACCOUNTING DATA CONTROL BLOCK) IS A CONTROL BLOCK
* LOCAL TO FLUOR WHICH IS USED TO STORE ACCOUNTING-ORIENTED DATA.
* THE ADCB IS LOCATED IN LSQA (SUBPOOL 255) AND IS POINTED TO BY
* JMRUCOM. THE ADCB IS CREATED BY THE SMF JOB INITIATION EXIT (IEFUJI)
* AND IS RELEASED BY THE SMF JOB TERMINATION EXIT (IEFACTRT). ITS
* PRIMARY PURPOSE IS TO SUPPLY DATA TO USER BILLING MESSAGES WHICH ARE
* WRITTEN WHEN ACCOUNTING PARAMETERS CHANGE WITHIN A JOB STEP.
*
*
ADCBHDR  DS    0CL32   HEADER INFORMATION
*
*      THE FOLLOWING FIELDS CONTAIN GENERAL INFORMATION WHICH IS
* OBTAINED AT JOB INITIALIZATION AND IS NOT CHANGED. IT IS OBTAINED
* FROM THE SMF COMMON EXIT PARAMETER AREA.
*
ADCBJOBN DS    CL8     JOB NAME
ADCBRDRT DS    F       READER TIME (HUNDREDTHS OF SECONDS)
ADCBRDRD DS    PL4     READER DATE (JULIAN)
ADCBSID  DS    CL4     SYSTEM IDENTIFICATION
ADCBJES# DS    CL8     JES2 JOB NUMBER
ADCBSTP# DS    XL1     NUMBER OF THE STEP BEING PROCESSED
ADCBSMFL DS    XL1     SMF OPTION FLAGS
ADCBRSTR DS    XL1     RESTART INDICATOR
ADCBCLS  DS    CL1     JOB CLASS
*
*
ADCBCNTL DS    0CL60   CONTROL INFORMATION
*
*      THE FOLLOWING FIELDS CONTAIN CONTROL INFORMATION WHICH IS MAIN-
* TAINED FOR THE DURATION OF THE JOB. MOST OF THIS DATA IS OBTAINED
* FROM THE JOB CARD.
*
ADCBJD0  DS    CL20    JOB DESCRIPTION (PROGRAMMER NAME)
ADCBCON0 DS    CL6     CONTRACT
         DS    CL2     RESERVED
ADCBAU0  DS    CL4     AREA/UNIT
ADCBCNG0 DS    CL3     CHANGE ORDER
         DS    CL1     RESERVED
ADCBENT0 DS    CL2     ENTITY
         DS    CL2     RESERVED
ADCBORG0 DS    CL3     ORGANIZATION
         DS    CL1     RESERVED
ADCBOPR0 DS    CL3     OPERATION
         DS    CL1     RESERVED
ADCBJOB0 DS    CL5     FLUOR JOB NUMBER
ADCBADXB DS    XL3     PTR TO ADXB
ADCBDYN0 DS    F       DYNAMIC ALLOCATION EXCPS FOR JOB STEP
*
*
ADCBENT1 DS    0CL80   ACCOUNTING STATS AT PREVIOUS PARAMETER CHANGE
*
*      THE FOLLOWING FIELDS CONTAIN SYSTEM MEASUREMENTS AT THE TIME OF
* THE PREVIOUS CHANGE IN ACCOUNTING PARAMETERS. ALL MEASUREMENTS BUT
* CPU TIMES REPRESENT ACCUMULATIONS FOR THE JOB.
*
ADCBTCB1 DS    F       TCB TIME
ADCBSRB1 DS    F       SRB TIME
ADCBEXC1 DS    F       EXCP COUNT
ADCBSRV1 DS    F       SERVICE UNIT COUNT
ADCBCON1 DS    CL6     CONTRACT
         DS    CL2     RESERVED
ADCBAU1  DS    CL4     AREA/UNIT
ADCBCNG1 DS    CL3     CHANGE ORDER
         DS    CL1     RESERVED
ADCBPGM1 DS    CL8     PROGRAM
ADCBCRG1 DS    CL7     CHARGE SCHEDULE ID
         DS    CL1     RESERVED
ADCBF1B1 DS    E       BILLING FACTOR #1
ADCBF2B1 DS    E       BILLING FACTOR #2
ADCBF3B1 DS    E       BILLING FACTOR #3
ADCBTIM1 DS    F       TIME OF DAY THIS CALL WAS MADE
ADCBDAT1 DS    F       DATE THIS CALL WAS MADE
ADCBLCT1 DS    F       LINE COUNT
ADCBRSV1 DS    2F      RESERVED FOR FUTURE USE
*
*
ADCBENT2 DS    0CL80   ACCOUNTING STATS AT CURRENT PARAMETER CHANGE
*
*      THE FOLLOWING FIELDS CONTAIN SYSTEM MEASUREMENTS AT THE TIME OF
* THE CURRENT CHANGE IN ACCOUNTING PARAMETERS. ALL MEASUREMENTS BUT
* CPU TIMES REPRESENT ACCUMULATIONS FOR THE JOB.
*
ADCBTCB2 DS    F       TCB TIME
ADCBSRB2 DS    F       SRB TIME
ADCBEXC2 DS    F       EXCP COUNT
ADCBSRV2 DS    F       SERVICE UNIT COUNT
ADCBCON2 DS    CL6     CONTRACT
         DS    CL2     RESERVED
ADCBAU2  DS    CL4     AREA/UNIT
ADCBCNG2 DS    CL3     CHANGE ORDER
         DS    CL1     RESERVED
ADCBPGM2 DS    CL8     PROGRAM
ADCBCRG2 DS    CL7     CHARGE SCHEDULE ID
         DS    CL1     RESERVED
ADCBF1B2 DS    E       BILLING FACTOR #1
ADCBF2B2 DS    E       BILLING FACTOR #2
ADCBF3B2 DS    E       BILLING FACTOR #3
ADCBTIM2 DS    F       TIME OF DAY THIS CALL WAS MADE
ADCBDAT2 DS    F       DATE THIS CALL WAS MADE
ADCBLCT2 DS    F       LINE COUNT
ADCBRSV2 DS    2F      RESERVED FOR FUTURE USE
*
ADCBEND  EQU   *
ADCBLEN  EQU   ADCBEND-ADCBDATA
         MEND
